===Instruction execution===
Each instruction is executed in steps that are usually termed [[machine cycle]]s (M-cycles), each of which can take between three and six clock periods (T-states).<ref>{{cite book | title = Z80 Family CPU User Manual | author = Zilog | publisher = Zilog | date = 2005 | page = 11 |url=http://www.zilog.com/docs/z80/um0080.pdf }}</ref> Each M-cycle corresponds roughly to one memory access or internal operation. Many instructions actually end during the M1 of the ''next'' instruction which is known as a ''fetch/execute overlap''.

